00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:03.666
So we said, what should you
do--I'm going to do the

00:07:03.666 --> 00:07:05.680
calculation now a little bit
differently--

00:07:05.680 --> 00:07:10.379
I said after every payment of
8.88 you could always say to

00:07:10.379 --> 00:07:13.413
yourself,
"Do I want to continue or

00:07:13.413 --> 00:07:15.730
do I want to pay my
option?"

00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:19.649
Now, you notice that if I had
divided this by B_1,

00:07:19.649 --> 00:07:23.370
say, if you had a mortgage that
was a little bit smaller,

00:07:23.370 --> 00:07:30.670
barely over a 1 dollar for
example,

00:07:30.670 --> 00:07:33.190
that would divide everything by
B_1.

00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:36.261
The payments would all be
divided by B_1 and the

00:07:36.261 --> 00:07:39.440
remaining balances would all be
divided by B_1.

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:41.410
So I could always scale this
thing up or down.

00:07:41.410 --> 00:07:45.791
There's nothing fancy about
100, nothing important about

00:07:45.791 --> 00:07:46.269
100.
 

00:07:46.269 --> 00:07:49.872
If the original loan was for
200 you just double all your

00:07:49.872 --> 00:07:53.089
payments and double all your
remaining balances.

00:07:53.089 --> 00:07:54.440
What could be more obvious than
that?

00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:57.927
So I want to think in those
terms of a mortgage that always

00:07:57.927 --> 00:07:59.129
has 1 dollar left.
 

00:07:59.129 --> 00:08:05.000
So suppose at any stage you had
1 dollar left in your mortgage.

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:08.689
Your remaining balance was 1.
 

00:08:08.689 --> 00:08:18.968
So let's say at any node,
let's ask the question,

00:08:18.968 --> 00:08:30.319
what is the value of 1 dollar
of remaining balance?

00:08:30.319 --> 00:08:33.315
So if you start at 100 and you
haven't prepaid,

00:08:33.315 --> 00:08:35.918
here you've got B_2
dollars.

00:08:35.918 --> 00:08:38.586
Of course, whatever the value
of that is divided by

00:08:38.586 --> 00:08:41.038
B_2,
that's the value of 1 dollar.

00:08:41.038 --> 00:08:45.267
So I'm just going to figure out
the value of 1 dollar of

00:08:45.267 --> 00:08:48.803
remaining balance and I'm going
to call that W,

00:08:48.803 --> 00:08:49.879
let's say.
 

00:08:49.879 --> 00:08:52.370
I'll call that W of some node S.
 

00:08:52.370 --> 00:08:53.580
So where am I?
 

00:08:53.580 --> 00:08:59.254
I'm in some node in this
interest rate tree,

00:08:59.254 --> 00:09:00.308
right?
 

00:09:00.308 --> 00:09:03.528
Here's our interest rate tree,
and I'm anywhere just here,

00:09:03.528 --> 00:09:06.389
and I'm doing backward
induction so for all successor

00:09:06.389 --> 00:09:09.690
nodes I figured out what 1
dollar of remaining balance is.

00:09:09.690 --> 00:09:16.921
And let's say it's in period
1,2, 3,4, 5, so I'm in period 5,

00:09:16.921 --> 00:09:18.850
B_5.
 

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:21.620
So what is the remaining
balance at this node which I

00:09:21.620 --> 00:09:22.100
call S?
 

00:09:22.100 --> 00:09:27.860
So it's some node right there
of--oh no, I've lost it.

00:09:27.860 --> 00:09:32.470
So W_S is going to be
what?

00:09:32.470 --> 00:09:38.775
It's going to be the minimum of
1, you could just pay it if you

00:09:38.775 --> 00:09:41.928
wanted to, or you could wait.
 

00:09:41.928 --> 00:09:46.923
1 over (1 r_S),
and then what would you have to

00:09:46.923 --> 00:09:50.669
do, you would have to make your
payment.

00:09:50.669 --> 00:09:52.149
Well, what's your payment?
 

00:09:52.149 --> 00:10:08.250
The payment is this 8.88 but
divided by B_5 plus

00:10:08.250 --> 00:10:18.418
the remaining balance of 1
dollar.

00:10:18.418 --> 00:10:25.498
So (B_6 over
B_5) times the

00:10:25.498 --> 00:10:30.730
remainder times W_Sup.
 

00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:32.740
Now, why is this right?
 

00:10:32.740 --> 00:10:34.129
I hope it is right by the way.
 

00:10:34.129 --> 00:10:41.798
I should have thought of this a
little before.

00:10:41.798 --> 00:10:44.658
So this is the remainder of 1
dollar left.

00:10:44.658 --> 00:10:47.639
So if I divide by B_5
here I'm not going to have a

00:10:47.639 --> 00:10:49.509
remaining balance of
B_6.

00:10:49.509 --> 00:10:54.274
I'm going to have a remaining
balance of B_6 over

00:10:54.274 --> 00:10:55.590
B_5.
 

00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:59.576
So if I started with 1 dollar
of remaining balance then I know

00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:03.431
that in the next period I'm
going to have B_6 over

00:11:03.431 --> 00:11:06.830
B_5 dollars of
remaining balance left.

00:11:06.830 --> 00:11:16.528
It doesn't sound too
convincing, by the way.

00:11:16.528 --> 00:11:19.053
Well, it's right,
and that happens with

00:11:19.053 --> 00:11:20.450
probability 1 half.
 

00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:24.350
And then with the other
probability 1 half,

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:29.879
plus I make the payment,
but I go down instead of up and

00:11:29.879 --> 00:11:35.106
so I have B_6 over
B_5 but I have

00:11:35.106 --> 00:11:41.700
W_Sdown,
and that's also times 1 half.

00:11:41.700 --> 00:11:48.133
So either I pay off my
remaining dollar or I end up

00:11:48.133 --> 00:11:51.350
with this many dollars.
 

00:11:51.350 --> 00:11:55.340
Assuming I had a 1 dollar of
remaining balance I'm either

00:11:55.340 --> 00:11:58.357
going to pay it off,
the remaining balance,

00:11:58.357 --> 00:12:02.240
or I'm going to have this much
left next period and 1 dollar of

00:12:02.240 --> 00:12:04.809
remaining balance is going to be
that.

00:12:04.809 --> 00:12:07.470
So that's it.
 

00:12:07.470 --> 00:12:11.599
So I know now by working this
backwards I can tell what 1

00:12:11.599 --> 00:12:14.178
dollar at the beginning is
worth.

00:12:14.178 --> 00:12:17.015
And so it's exactly the same
calculation I did before except

00:12:17.015 --> 00:12:18.408
I'm talking about 1 dollar.
 

00:12:18.408 --> 00:12:21.125
I'm always figuring out 1
dollar of remaining balance

00:12:21.125 --> 00:12:22.639
instead of the whole thing.
 

00:12:22.639 --> 00:12:25.779
Present value of callable,
so here's present value of 1

00:12:25.779 --> 00:12:27.058
dollar of principal.
 

00:12:27.058 --> 00:12:31.565
And so remember the present
