00:13:04.028 --> 00:13:07.105
If I do it all in terms of 1
dollar of remaining balance then

00:13:07.105 --> 00:13:10.230
just by looking at the screen I
can tell where the guy prepaid

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:11.820
because there are 1s there.
 

00:13:11.820 --> 00:13:13.288
So I know where he's prepaid.
 

00:13:13.288 --> 00:13:15.460
Wherever the 1s are that means
he's prepaid.

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:17.509
So I can tell very easily what
he did.

00:13:17.509 --> 00:13:20.779
All right, that's the only
purpose of doing the same

00:13:20.779 --> 00:13:23.408
calculation in a somewhat
trickier way.

00:13:23.408 --> 00:13:26.085
So if you think about it a
second you see I've just divided

00:13:26.085 --> 00:13:28.899
by--I've always reduced things
to if you had 1 dollar left.

00:13:28.899 --> 00:13:32.101
All right, so this tells us
what to do, when the guy should

00:13:32.101 --> 00:13:34.200
prepay and when he shouldn't
prepay.

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:38.620
So if you're now in the world
