00:29:40.453 --> 00:29:40.838
what.
 

00:29:40.838 --> 00:29:43.657
People have to prepay,
and why is it that people never

00:29:43.657 --> 00:29:46.529
prepay more than 60 percent
historically or 70 percent,

00:29:46.529 --> 00:29:48.710
because not everybody pays
attention.

00:29:48.710 --> 00:29:51.103
Now, I called them the dumb
guys last time,

00:29:51.103 --> 00:29:53.269
but as I said,
I probably fit into that

00:29:53.269 --> 00:29:54.009
category.
 

00:29:54.009 --> 00:29:56.220
It's people who are distracted
and doing other things.

00:29:56.220 --> 00:29:58.045
They're just not paying
attention and so they don't

00:29:58.045 --> 00:29:58.410
realize.
 

00:29:58.410 --> 00:30:00.585
They don't know what's going
on, so they don't realize they

00:30:00.585 --> 00:30:01.410
should be prepaying.
 

00:30:01.410 --> 00:30:03.568
So as interest rates go down
more people prepay.

00:30:03.568 --> 00:30:05.348
As interest rates go up less
people prepay.

00:30:05.348 --> 00:30:09.032
And if you did some historical
thing and figured out the right

00:30:09.032 --> 00:30:11.750
parameters you'd get a
prepayment function.

00:30:11.750 --> 00:30:14.420
So how did I figure out this
was 15?

00:30:14.420 --> 00:30:16.390
How did I figure out this was
.6?

00:30:16.390 --> 00:30:18.720
Why should I divide this by 133?
 

00:30:18.720 --> 00:30:19.630
What's sigma?
 

00:30:19.630 --> 00:30:23.386
Once you get those parameters
historically you now have a

00:30:23.386 --> 00:30:27.950
