00:33:56.130 --> 00:34:00.319
Should the pool that's left be
worth 40 percent of the pool

00:34:00.319 --> 00:34:03.715
that you had just here,
or more than 40 percent,

00:34:03.715 --> 00:34:05.740
or less than 40 percent?
 

00:34:05.740 --> 00:34:08.489
So remember,
you had 100 people here.

00:34:08.489 --> 00:34:10.960
You're the bank who's lent them
the money.

00:34:10.960 --> 00:34:13.639
You're valuing the mortgage
payments they're going to make

00:34:13.639 --> 00:34:15.438
to you,
you're getting a certain amount

00:34:15.438 --> 00:34:18.353
of money from them,
60 percent of them suddenly

00:34:18.353 --> 00:34:21.409
disappeared in 1 month leaving
40 left,

00:34:21.409 --> 00:34:25.190
but now interest rates are back
exactly where they were before.

00:34:25.190 --> 00:34:27.849
Is the value of the mortgage
starting here with the 40

00:34:27.849 --> 00:34:30.809
percent pool worth 40 percent of
what it was originally,

00:34:30.809 --> 00:34:32.980
more than 40 percent or less
than 40 percent?

00:34:32.980 --> 00:34:33.940
